The paper deals with distributed algorithms for network topology discovery and message delivery, which are core topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the issue of Byzantine fault tolerance, which is a common concern in cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a self-stabilizing algorithm, which is a technique used in control theory (cs.SY) to ensure that a system can recover from any transient faults.
